To build this service, we will first need to create an Employee class in Java Spring Boot. This class will include private variables for each field: first_name, last_name, employee_id, email, and title. It will also contain getter and setter methods for each variable. Additionally, we will need a structure or a repository class to manage the full list of employees.

Next, we will create a Controller class. This class is responsible for handling database interactions using standard HTTP commands. Users will send a GET command to acquire the full list of user data, while the POST command will be used to add an individual user. Furthermore, the DELETE command will remove an entry, and the PUT command will be used to update an existing entry.

